alwaysApply: true
---

UI implemented using Dioxus in crate `backoffice-dioxus`.

Rules:

- Views are container components.
- Child components are presentation-only.
- Avoid waterfall requests using streams and/or try_join!.
- Components must not contain business logic.
- Components call custom hooks.
- Custom hooks call use cases.
- Use cases call outbound adapters.
- Avoid raw RSX when a Dioxus component already exists from: https://dioxuslabs.com/components
- All texts must be translatable using .flt files, which are in the i18n folder, so keys will be used to identify strings, including error strings.
- app_context.rs acts as a dependency container.

Examples reference:

- use_action
  views/login.rs
  ui/hooks/login.rs
- use_resource
  views/specialist_dashboard.rs
  hooks/specialist_patients.rs
- parallel requests in crate `application`:
  use_cases/patient_progress.rs
  use_cases/submit_patient_workout_feedback.rs
